<L>__{exterior terrace of the hotel night}
<A>__{enzo sits at the grand piano in the corner of the terrace. beethoven was always a favorite of his. jacques, very tipsy by now walks over, a glass in each hand. he hands enzo a glass, then takes off his tennis shoes and sits them neatly on the piano.}
<C>__{enzo}
<D>__{there is nothing like music. it speaks from the heart. can you tell me why we bother diving in the dark, the cold, without ever taking the time to breathe? huh? can you tell me why we do it?}
<A>__{jacques nods.}
<C>__{enzo}
<D>__{why?}
<C>__{jacques}
<D>__{... for the mermaids.}
<A>__{enzo smiles, moved.}
<C>__{enzo}
<D>__{my father used to see them everywhere too... but the only one he ever caught was my mother... actually she caught him.}
